11:
You serve a traitor. He killed the last 
Lord of the Oasis. He must answer for 
his crimes!
16: Then tell us! Where is he?
20: I don't know! He just disappeared...
26:
This is my palace. You like it?
Kind of tacky, if you ask me.
34:
I mean, nobles have to show off 
a little. But you know what the best 
part about this place is?
38: It's my first time here. Just tell me.
44:
Nuh-uh! Look at you, always wanting 
to jump straight to the answer.
47:
But putting together the puzzle's half 
the fun! And when you finally see the 
whole picture—that'll be a day to 
remember.
51:
...I figured out your puzzle a long time 
ago.
61:
Is it just me, or does this place look 
awfully familiar?
65:
Ruins, sleeping beneath a palace. 
...Or was the palace MEANT to be built 
atop these ruins? But if so, why?
68:
Why else, but to hide the World 
Flipper?
72:
You've no idea how surprised I was 
when I found out. Selfish Rolan, 
concealing such a delectable toy in 
his basement.
74:
He KNEW the royal family's long 
wanted to study the civilization 
behind these ruins. Tut tut... What a 
breach of trust.
82:
Well, he betrayed us. And when you 
betray royalty, that's called treason.
92:
He was an imbecile who chose a BEAST 
over FAMILY! The sand beneath my feet 
was worth more than him!
114:
Ahaha! As long as I am lord of the 
land, the power of the Custodians is 
MINE.
116: There live none who can defy me!
126:
When I'm done with you, you're gonna 
be begging Rolan for forgiveness—on 
the other side!
